# ResourceManagerSystem

## Purpose
On the first frame, loads all textures, fonts, shaders, UI layouts, sound clips, JSON assets, 3D
models, render targets, and the text-to-image model assets (checkpoints, LoRAs, ControlNets, OpenPose
skeletons) from `Assets/Engine/ResourcesManifest.json` and `Assets/App/ResourcesManifest.json`, then
creates ResourceMapSingletonComponent containing the fully populated asset maps. On every subsequent
frame it drains any RegisterGeneratedTextureRequest, registering each generated image as a Texture2D in
the existing texture map under its caller-assigned UUID (so a generated image becomes an ordinary
texture). The first-frame load is guarded by a presence check; the registration drain runs in steady
state.

Render targets are pathless manifest entries (`{id, width, height}`): the created offscreen target is
stored in the render-target map and its colour buffer is registered in the texture map under the same
UUID, so 2D draws can sample the 3D pass's output as an ordinary texture (ADR 0007).

Checkpoints/LoRAs/ControlNets are recorded as resolved file paths only (the diffusion backend loads the
weights, not the engine); OpenPose skeletons are parsed into pose resources. Generated images arrive as
RGB and are expanded to RGBA when registered as textures (ADR 0008).

## Input Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| ResourceMapSingletonComponent | read / write | Presence-check guards the one-time load; in steady state generated textures are inserted into the existing map |
| RegisterGeneratedTextureRequestOneFrameComponent | read | Each carries a generated image + target UUID to register as a texture |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| ResourceMapSingletonComponent | write / add (deferred) | Created once with all asset maps (textures, shaders, fonts, UI layouts, sounds, JSON, models, render targets, checkpoints, LoRAs, ControlNets, OpenPose skeletons); thereafter modified in place to register generated textures |
